<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="426" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1137,1632]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1317,1344]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[853,999,1317,1343]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1043,1346,1317,1344]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" pagination="383 - 394" refId="ref28384" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2006) The Ephydridae (Diptera: Brachycera: Muscomorpha) of south-western Saudi Arabia. Fauna of Arabia, 21, 383 - 394." type="journal article" year="2006">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and El- Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[260,309,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">et al</emphasis>
. (2019). The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[772,839,1354,1380]" name="Egypt" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Egypt</collectingCountry>
(Elephant Island on the 
<collectingRegion box="[1111,1223,1353,1379]" country="Sudan" name="Nahr an Nil" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">river Nile</collectingRegion>
; hence the name of the genus) and further recorded from the Afrotropical Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[841,911,1389,1415]" name="Sudan" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1209,1389,1415]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
; Palaearctic Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[151,238,1425,1451]" name="Algeria" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[248,318,1426,1452]" name="Egypt" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[327,392,1425,1451]" name="Israel" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Israel</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[402,477,1425,1451]" name="Jordan" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Jordan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[529,676,1425,1451]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. There are some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Mathis &amp; Zatwarnicki" authorityYear="1995" box="[1012,1206,1425,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Eremotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspiciendum">
<emphasis box="[1012,1206,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">E. perspiciendum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NMWC collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,279,1461,1487]" name="Niger" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Niger</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[289,376,1461,1487]" name="Nigeria" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[387,455,1461,1487]" name="Oman" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Oman</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[509,591,1462,1488]" name="Yemen" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Yemen</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="426" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1137,1632]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1498,1524]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Mathis &amp; Zatwarnicki" authorityYear="1995" box="[318,509,1497,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Eremotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspiciendum">
<emphasis box="[318,509,1497,1523]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">E. perspiciendum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite distinct from 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1903" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1903" box="[742,1003,1497,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Eremotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chnumi">
<emphasis box="[742,852,1497,1523]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">E. chnumi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Becker, T." box="[857,1003,1497,1523]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" pagination="67 - 195" refId="ref26115" refString="Becker, T. (1903) Aegyptische Dipteren Gesammelt und Beschrieben (Fortsetzung und Schluss). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 2 (1), 67 - 195." type="journal article" year="1903">Becker, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1051,1098,1498,1524]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, described in the same paper but was transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1896" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1896" box="[695,990,1533,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Allotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[695,840,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Allotrichoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Becker, T." box="[846,990,1533,1559]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" pagination="91 - 276" refId="ref26039" refString="Becker, T. (1896) Dipterologische Studien IV. Ephydridae. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 41, 91 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 48018960505" type="journal article" year="1896">Becker, 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and later became the species upon which the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Giordani Soika, 1956" authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1956" box="[298,707,1569,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Eremotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,469,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Eremotrichoma</emphasis>
Giordani Soika, 1956
</taxonomicName>
was established. Through misidentification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Mathis &amp; Zatwarnicki" authorityYear="1995" box="[1213,1404,1569,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Eremotrichoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspiciendum">
<emphasis box="[1213,1230,1570,1595]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1404,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">perspiciendum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Cresson and others, the situation became very complicated but was clarified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathis, W. N. &amp; Deeming, J. C." box="[1023,1317,1605,1631]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" pagination="562 - 570" refId="ref31554" refString="Mathis, W. N. &amp; Deeming, J. C. (1987) A revision of the shore fly genus Elephantinosoma Becker (Diptera: Ephydridae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 89 (3), 562 - 570." type="journal article" year="1987">Mathis &amp; Deeming (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
